A calendar with cohort information and letter days was sent to all parents, and it can be found on our website: https://www.sandycreekcsd.org/pub/1080

White Comets will be expected to engage remotely on Sept. 8. Middle and high school students should check their emails for information from teachers prior to the start of school.

post_text: It is a time-honored tradition at Sandy Creek Central School for the Senior class President to hand the spade down to the Junior class President at the Junior Senior Prom. This year our prom was canceled due to the Covid 19 Pandemic. In true Creeker fashion we persevered and made this tradition happen while looking forward to better days! We try to always remember "life is good!" It is our honor to present to you Marley Yerdon and Deanna Hathway for the annual handing down of the spade. -Senior Class Advisors Tonya Trudell and Michelle Shirley

post_text:
ALERT: The last day of school for Sandy Creek students is Thursday, June 18.

Many of our students have been able to retrieve their personal belongings over the past couple of weeks. To help both students and families, we will be returning all unclaimed bags to students on Monday, June 1 as part of the meal delivery bus route.

We also have plans in place for high school graduation. A letter describing the ceremony, along with supporting information will be sent to all parents of our graduates after it is approved by the Oswego County Health Department.

If you are a parent or caregiver who needs child care, please complete this parent need for child care survey. It can be found at: https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/3HSNNYJ

Based on the information you provide about your job, employer, number of children, and financial need, the Office of Children and Family Services (OCFS) may be able to help you find the child program you need. It may be a challenge to find child care due to COVID-19 related program closures, however the staff at OCFS are trying their best to support families to find the high quality child care that they need.

The survey is in English, they are currently being translated, translations to follow.

Additional links-
Link to the YMCA Emergency Child Care: www.emergencychildcareny.org

In addition, the OCFS website has several resources available: https://ocfs.ny.gov/programs/childcare/

post_text:
Good morning! This is a message to let you know that meals will continue to be delivered this week on Monday, Wednesday and Thursday. Please continue to have a plastic tote, cardboard box or cooler at the end of your driveway for the food to be placed in. On Monday and Thursday, we will supply double breakfast and lunch, so be sure to have a large enough container. Meals leave here around 9:30 a.m. and will arrive between 9:45-noon each morning.

Additionally, even though teaching staff are not in the building this week, they are happy to help via email! You can find their email address on the school website at https://www.sandycreekcsd.org/district/staff. If you have any issues with the Chromebooks, please reach out to the help desk.

We will continue to provide updates as we gain more information. Thank you and have a nice day.

post_text:
This Saturday (March 21), staff will be handing out Chromebooks from 9 a.m. to 1 p.m in the High School Gym for all third through 12th grade Sandy Creek CSD students that require one to complete academic tasks for school. Please note, K-2 students will NOT be given an electronic device.

These Chromebooks are only for students who have a registered Chromebook with the Sandy Creek CSD. If you already have your own device at home that your child can use, then you do not have to participate in this program.

Parents will be able to sign out the Chromebooks in groups of 10 to meet state requirements for social distancing. During this time, no students will be able to pick up any other personal belongings.

Good morning! Please be advised that beginning today (3.18.20) our buses will leave the school around 9:30 a.m. to deliver food. In an effort to limit exposure and protect the food, we are asking that each family leave a cooler, plastic tote or box at the end of the driveway so we can place the food in them.

Beginning next week, we will deliver food on Monday, Wednesday and Thursday. Monday and Thursday, we will double up the food so each child will have breakfast and lunch for all five days.

Thank you for your understanding and cooperation. We truly appreciate it.

COMETS CELEBRATE VETERANS DAY: Sandy Creek held two ceremonies this afternoon, celebrating and commemorating local veterans.

In the Elementary School, the Fort Drum Color Guard displayed the colors in front of a crowd filled with veterans and students during a program that highlighted the importance of those who help defend our country. The MS/HS students heard tremendous, passionate essays from three of our students who wrote about what makes America such a great country.

We are incredibly proud of our caring, passionate students. Thank you to all who have served or are serving, happy Veterans Day!

This month, we are showcasing our CTE Computer Coding and Culinary Arts programs! Computer Coding sets the foundation of computer language including HTML, CSS, and Javascript. Students will also get to work on mobile app development, remote server workflow and data queries. The job market is fantastic for computers right now! Students in Culinary Arts get real-life experience in food preparation in a state-of-the-art industrial kitchen. Interested in learning more? Our open house is October 17 from 6-7:30 PM!
